0.body: fmerge is a tool that allows merging files recursively and with custom placeholder patterns. The include file statements are always relative to the file that includes them.
0.title: fmerge

12.body: This project makes use of https://semver.org[the semver v2 versioning scheme] for all parts of the official public API. The public stable API is a subset of all available features (see link:/fmerge/docs/adrs/4-experimental-flag[this page]).
12.title: 3: Versioning

13.body: There is a application level argument (flag) experimental (-e | --experimental) that indicates that experimental features can now be accessed. This flag explicitly marks features that are NOT part of the official public API and therefore NOT considered when applying the versioning scheme (see link:/fmerge/docs/adrs/3-versioning[ADR 3]). + This flag is designed to be used with and therefore CAN be used with link:/fmerge/docs/adrs/5-feature-flags[feature Flags as specified in ADR 5].
13.title: 4: Experimental flag

14.body: This project makes use of cargo feature flags. Feature flags count as part of the public API and are therefore to be considered when applying the version rules IF NOT marked as experimental (see link:/fmerge/docs/adrs/4-experimental-flag[ADR 4]). + All feature flags MUST be documented in an appropriate manner in the documentation.
14.title: 5: Feature flags

4.body: This document contains the help content for the fmerge command-line program. Command Overview: fmerge↴ fmerge man↴ fmerge autocomplete↴ fmerge merge↴
4.title: Command-Line Help for fmerge

5.body: A rusty text templating application for CLIs. Usage: fmerge [OPTIONS] <COMMAND> Subcommands: man — Renders the manual. autocomplete — Renders shell completion scripts. merge — Merge. Options: -e, --experimental <EXPERIMENTAL> — enables experimental features
5.title: fmerge

6.body: Renders the manual. Usage: fmerge man --out <out> --format <format> Options: -o, --out <OUT> -f, --format <FORMAT> Possible values: manpages, markdown
6.title: fmerge man

7.body: Renders shell completion scripts. Usage: fmerge autocomplete --out <out> --shell <shell> Options: -o, --out <OUT> -s, --shell <SHELL> Possible values: bash, zsh, fish, elvish, powershell
7.title: fmerge autocomplete

8.body: Merge. Usage: fmerge merge [OPTIONS] --file <file> --pattern <pattern> Options: -f, --file <FILE> -p, --pattern <PATTERN> --placeholder <PLACEHOLDER> Default value: %f This document was generated automatically by clap-markdown.
8.title: fmerge merge
